# dig

To drive a dig knowledge base, follow the canonical instruction set — the
portable dig skill: `skills/dig/SKILL.md` in the dig repo
(https://github.com/vllnt/dig/blob/main/skills/dig/SKILL.md), and the
integration contract `docs/integration.md`.

In short: `dig --version` to detect (install from https://dig.vllnt.com); a KB
is a directory with a `.dig/` folder (`dig init`, `--kb <path>`). Read with
`dig find "<q>" --json` (`--mode hybrid` for semantic), `dig drift --json`,
`dig log --json`, `dig export --json`. Mutate via `dig org --dry-run` → `dig
org`, `dig reconcile`, `dig undo` — preview first; everything is reversible.
Parse `--json`; never scrape human output.

Or register the MCP server (`dig mcp`) in Cursor's MCP settings and call the
`dig_*` tools directly.
